Von Oettingen shows that, according to Dr. Ryan, 12,000 to 14,000 prostitutes in London became such as a consequence of a neglected childhood.Op. cit., p. 216. In the “Reports of the Select Committee,” etc., the following figures are found:Appendix B, p. 52. of 3,075 prostitutes 1,481 (48%) were orphans, and 921 (29%) were half-orphans. In his “La prostitution clandestine à Paris”, Dr. Commenge gives the following figures concerning the 2,368 prostitutes whom he observed during the years from 1878 to 1887:P. 42.
692 (29%) were orphans;
456 (19%) had lost their mother;
